ROADMAP
=======

Feature roadmap. It lists most fo the currently planned features and 
details the schedule for release.

These are not hard deadlines and things are subject to change. Please
feel free to suggest features, contribute, or comment.

0.9.0

* Nested alias [AS GOOD AS DONE]
* Import of Mud Connectfiles [DONE]
* Save logfiles of mud-traffic [DONE]
* Rewrite connection wizard step 1 [DONE]
	+ double click on entries to connect [DONE]
* Rewrite font/color support [DONE]
* Right-click menu for connection-tabs
* Make better use for gtk_object_(get|set)_data [DONE]
* Cleanup of .c-files, better names on functions, etc... [DONE]
* Fix error when closing wizardwindow after using profilewindow [DONE]
* Scriptingsupport (python) [DONE]
* Page Up, Page Down and Mousewheel support [DONE]
* Fix Segfault in delete keybind [DONE]

0.10.0

* GNOME 2.0
* Use splitscreen feature from next version (1.4/2.0) of GTK
* AutoReconnect
* Get more speed in ANSI
* Support for TELNET codes [PARTLY DONE]

0.11.0

* Rewrite connection wizard step 2 [DONE]
	+ be able to ping host...
	+ several characters per host
* MSP, Mud Sound Protocol (Is there many muds using this?)
* SOCKS support
* IPv6 support


Long term future

* Option for nr of lines to keep in buffer
* Fix MCCP (crashes on a few muds)
* Green/Red marker, so that you can see if tab is connected or not
* Other marker on tab to show if using MCCP or not
* Fix Speedwalking in AutoMapper
* User defineable buttonbar
* Customizable statusline
* Tab completion, and separate history for each connection
* Make it run on Windows

